Employee Performance & Retention Dashboard

Project Overview
The Employee Performance & Retention Dashboard is an analytical tool built in Excel to help HR and management teams monitor workforce performance, engagement, and attrition patterns.  
This project provides clear insights into how employee performance, training, and tenure impact overall retention and productivity.


Objective
The main goal of this dashboard is to:
- Analyze employee performance across departments.
- Identify key retention risks and attrition trends.
- Measure training effectiveness and engagement levels.
- Enable data-driven decisions for employee development and retention strategies.


Tools & Technologies
- Microsoft Excel  — for dashboard development  
- PivotTables, Charts, and Slicers — for interactivity  
- Data Cleaning & Transformation — using Excel formulas and structured tables  

Key Insights & Analysis
- Average Performance Score: 77.17 across all departments.  
- Top Performing Department: Marketing with an average score of ~85.  
- Employee Status: 83% active, 17% on probation.  
- Retention Risk Distribution: 46% medium risk, 13% high risk.  
- Average Monthly Sales: ₹3.38 lakh across all departments.  
- Join Date Trend: Most employees joined during 2019–2021.  


How This Dashboard Helps
- Helps HR managers identify departments with low performance or high attrition.  
- Enables proactive employee engagement initiatives based on risk levels.  
- Supports data-driven workforce planning and training program optimization.  
- Acts as a single source of truth for key HR performance metrics.


Learnings
Through this project, I learned how to:
- Build an interactive and visually appealing HR analytics dashboard in Excel.
- Use pivot tables, conditional formatting, and slicers for interactivity.
- Translate HR metrics into actionable business insights.


